text: Kyzyl-Mayak () is a rural locality (a village) in Muraptalovsky Selsoviet, Kuyurgazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 40 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 41 km from Yermolayevo, 7 km from Novomuraptalovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kuyurgazinsky District
title: Kyzyl-Mayak
